Annotation providing a convenient and declarative mechanism for adding a {@link org.springframework.core.env.PropertySource PropertySource} to Spring's {@link org.springframework.core.env.Environment Environment}. To be used in conjunction with @{@link Configuration} classes.

Example usage

Given a file {@code app.properties} containing the keyvalue pair {@code testbean.name=myTestBean}, the following {@code @Configuration} class uses {@code @PropertySource} to contribute {@code app.properties} to the {@code Environment}'s set of {@code PropertySources}.

This annotation is repeatable according to Java 8 conventions.<b> However, all such {@code @PropertySource} annotations need to be declared at the same level: either directly on the configuration class or as meta-annotations on the same custom annotation. Mixing direct annotations and meta-annotations is not recommended since direct annotations will effectively override meta-annotations.
